						<summary>

						<p>Hero-stone (No. 6) set up in a field to the west of the village.</p>						

						<p>Permāḍi (?), circa 8th-9th century.</p>						

						<p>This record registers a gift of <hi rend="italic">kalnāḍu</hi> (land ?) by the king and the villagers, obviously to the family of <hi rend="bold">Rācha</hi> of <hi rend="bold">Beḷatūru,</hi> who died in a cattle-raid at Maṅgala. It refers to <hi rend="bold">Permāḍi</hi> as ruling the kingdom and <hi rend="bold">Mayimana Pallavareya</hi> as governing <hi rend="bold">Puli-nāḍu.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
